	<tr>
		<td colspan="2"><hr class="sep" />Yeah, the NES doesn't allow for sound expansions on the cartridges, the Famicom does. This means that there are games that generate sound on the cart, but when playing those on the NES these extra sounds are never output.

		

		</td>
	</tr>
	</table>


