	<tr>
		<td colspan="2"><hr class="sep" />Actually the NES has the sound I/O pins, but they are on the expansion port on the bottom.  So you could wire those 2 pins up to your adapter (and add those on the 60-pin adapter as well, since it won't exist normally).
<br />
<br />Unfortunately there is no "standard" sound mod, everyone uses a different one pretty much.  Even the common documented PowerPak one for one thing only uses a sound output and doesn't use input from the NES (why??).

		

		</td>
	</tr>
	</table>


